'''Salvador Bucca''' was professor of [[linguistics]] at the [[University of Buenos Aires]]. He was a [[Guggenheim fellow]] in 1958.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gf.org/fellows/all-fellows/salvador-bucca/|title=John Simon Guggenheim Foundation - Salvador Bucca|work=gf.org|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref> He was a specialist in the [[Kitsai language]] and the indigenous languages of Argentina. His papers and recordings relating to his work are stored in the Archive of the Indigenous Languages of Latin America at the [[University of Texas at Austin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ailla.utexas.org/islandora/object/ailla:124400|title=Archive of Indigenous Languages of Latin America|work=utexas.org|accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref> He donated materials on Chorote, Irish and Thai to the Laboratory of Documentation and Investigation of Linguistics and Anthropology in Buenos Aires.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.caicyt-conicet.gov.ar/micrositios/dila/?page_id=13|title=Lenguas Indígenas|work=caicyt-conicet.gov.ar|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>
==Selected publications== *Bucca, Salvador and Lesser, Alexander. 1969. "Kitsai Phonology and Morphophonemics". ''[[International Journal of American Linguistics]]'' 35. 7-20.
