{{About|the Vietnamese keyboarding software|the United States home security company|UniKey}} {{Infobox software | name = UniKey | logo = Unikeynt 101-4.png | logo caption = | logo size = | logo alt = | screenshot = Screenshot of UniKey 4.3 RC4.png | caption = UniKey 4.3 RC4 settings dialog | screenshot size = | screenshot alt = | author = | developer = Phạm Kim Long | released = {{Start date and age|2000|df=yes}}<!-- private releases back to 1994 don't count --><ref name="VNE Huy An">{{cite news|title=Bộ gõ tiếng Việt phổ biến nhất đã ra đời thế nào?|trans-title=How did the most popular Vietnamese input method editor come about?|author=Huy An|work=[[VnEconomy]]|publisher=Vietnam Economic Times|date=25 March 2014|accessdate=30 March 2015|url=http://vneconomy.vn/cuoc-song-so/bo-go-tieng-viet-pho-bien-nhat-da-ra-doi-the-nao-20140325111629153.htm|language=vi}}</ref> | discontinued = | latest release version = 4.3 RC4 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2018|7|14|df=yes}} | programming language = [[C++]] | operating system = [[Microsoft Windows]] | platform = | language = English, Vietnamese<ref name="Manual">{{cite web|title=Hướng dẫn sử dụng UniKey 3.5|trans-title=UniKey 3.5 User Guide|work=UniKey|date=April 2004|accessdate=30 March 2015|url=http://unikey.org/manual/ukmanual.htm|language=vi}}</ref> | genre = [[Input method editor]] | license = [[GNU General Public License]] | alexa = | website = {{URL|www.unikey.org}} | standard = }}
'''UniKey''' is an [[open-source software|open-source]] [[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]] [[input method editor]] for [[Microsoft Windows]] developed by Phạm Kim Long. {{As of|2014}}, it is the most popular input method editor for Vietnamese.<ref name="VNE Huy An"/> The official [[Linux]] port of UniKey is known as [[X-UniKey]].
==Features== UniKey supports the three most common Vietnamese input methods: [[Telex (input method)|Telex]], [[VNI#VNI Input Method|VNI]], and [[Vietnamese Quoted-Readable|VIQR]]. Due to the fragmented state of Vietnamese computing during the 1990s, UniKey supports as many as 14 Vietnamese [[character encoding]]s, including TCVN3 ([[VSCII]]), [[VNI#VNI Encoding|VNI]], [[Unicode]], [[VIQR]], VPS, [[VISCII]], and [[Windows-1258]].<ref name="Manual"/>
==History== Long began developing the software privately in 1994 as ''TVNBK'', short for ''{{lang|vi|Tiếng Việt Nam Bách Khoa}}'', after [[Hanoi University of Science and Technology]] (''{{lang|vi|Trường Đại học Bách khoa Hà Nội}}''), where he was studying. TVNBK was originally written in [[assembly language]] for [[DOS]] systems. In the mid-1990s, he ported it to [[Windows NT 4.0]], renaming it ''LittleVnKey''. In 2000, he released the software publicly for the first time as UniKey and placed it under the [[GNU General Public License]]. Recent versions of the software and its source code are hosted on [[SourceForge]].<ref name="VNE Huy An"/> Long has also developed [[VNG Corporation#Laban Key|Laban Key]], a popular Vietnamese input method editor for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]] devices that debuted in 2013.<ref name="VNE Huy An 2">{{cite news|title='Trận chiến' mới của cha đẻ Unikey|trans-title=A new "battle" for the father of Unikey|author=Huy An|work=VnEconomy|publisher=Vietnam Economic Times|date=26 March 2014|accessdate=30 March 2015|url=http://vneconomy.vn/cuoc-song-so/tran-chien-moi-cua-cha-de-unikey-20140326073532323.htm|language=vi}}</ref>
